OL,3,C'Why was this allowed to happen?':
OL,4,CSouthport mum demands answers
OL,6,FThe mother said that it hadn't been
OL,7,Funtil the first anniversary of the
OL,8,Fattack that her daughter had opened up
OL,9,Fto her counsellor about what happened.
OL,11,FShe told the inquiry: "To hear what
OL,12,Fshe said broke my heart but made me
OL,13,Fimmensely proud of her.
OL,15,F"The strength and bravery she showed,
OL,16,Falong with all of the girls there that
OL,17,Fday should be remembered and
OL,18,Facknowledged."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/8
